{"questionId":"7450","questionHtml":"<p>The graphs show the variation of the displacement <em>y</em> of a medium with distance <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and with time <em>t</em>&nbsp;for a travelling wave.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8265bd7ce072fab2e403c1ae90784e85ab2646d8.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the speed of the wave?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A.&nbsp; &nbsp;0.6 m s<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">B.&nbsp; &nbsp;0.8 m s<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">C.&nbsp; &nbsp;600 m s<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">D.&nbsp; &nbsp;800 m s<sup>–1</sup></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7450","referenceCode":"18N.1.SL.TZ0.15","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The graphs show the variation of the displacement y of a medium with distance x and with time t for a travelling wave. What is the speed of the wave? A. 0.6 m s–1 B. 0.8 m s–1 C. 6","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"15","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.1 – Measurements in physics","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}